-- Hungary May Choose Ader to Become Next President, Origo Reports
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2012-04-06T06:43:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/hungary-may-choose-ader-to-become-next-president-origo-reports.html
Hungary  may choose Janos Ader, a
former speaker of the country’s legislature and a current a
member of the European Parliament, to become its next president,
Origo  reported , citing unnamed government and ruling party
sources.  Ader has previously served as parliamentary group leader
and vice president of Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s ruling
party, Fidesz, the news website said.  Pal Schmitt this week became the first president to quit
since Hungary’s transition to democracy in 1990, after he was
stripped of his doctoral title for having plagiarized his thesis
two decades ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
